        <mxCell id="Jrw7hQ_IT_yxvlkLg96b-33" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;517&quot;&gt;The Patient Identification layer is used to connect incoming medical data to the correct patient in the CHMS. In the current implementation, the main working classes are &lt;code data-start=&quot;170&quot; data-end=&quot;185&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;PatientRecord&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code data-start=&quot;187&quot; data-end=&quot;196&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;Patient&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code data-start=&quot;202&quot; data-end=&quot;215&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;DataStorage&lt;/code&gt;. A &lt;code data-start=&quot;219&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;PatientRecord&lt;/code&gt; stores the measurement details, such as the patient ID, record type, measurement value, and timestamp. The &lt;code data-start=&quot;342&quot; data-end=&quot;351&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;Patient&lt;/code&gt; class represents one patient and contains a list of that patient’s records. &lt;code data-start=&quot;428&quot; data-end=&quot;441&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;DataStorage&lt;/code&gt; is responsible for storing patient data and retrieving records when needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;The diagram also shows extra identity-related classes: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;574&quot; data-end=&quot;593&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Helvetica&quot;&gt;PatientIdentifier&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;595&quot; data-end=&quot;613&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;IdentityMismatch&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;619&quot; data-end=&quot;636&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;IdentityManager&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. These are &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-start=&quot;648&quot; data-end=&quot;704&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;not actually implemented by us in the current system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, but they are included as possible future improvements. In the future, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;776&quot; data-end=&quot;795&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;PatientIdentifier&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; could be used to match the system’s &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;832&quot; data-end=&quot;843&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;patientId&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; with a real hospital patient ID. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;877&quot; data-end=&quot;894&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;IdentityManager&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; could verify incoming records before they are stored, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;953&quot; data-end=&quot;971&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;IdentityMismatch&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; could log cases where a patient ID does not match correctly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;This future design would make the system safer and more realistic, because data would only be stored after a valid patient match. However, for now, our implementation mainly focuses on storing and retrieving patient records using &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;1264&quot; data-end=&quot;1273&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Patient&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;1275&quot; data-end=&quot;1290&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;PatientRecord&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;1296&quot; data-end=&quot;1309&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Helvetica&quot;&gt;DataStorage&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="210" width="470" x="240" y="530" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
